# Prisma & Persistence

## Governance

Subordinate to `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md` and `architecture.mdc`. Mandatory workflow: `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc`.

| Document | Path |
|----------|------|
| AI Constitution | `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md` |
| Workflow | `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc` |
| Universal agent instructions | `AGENTS.md` |
| Project context skill | `.claude/skills/project-context/SKILL.md` |

Prisma only in infrastructure. Schema changes require database impact analysis (workflow Step 3).

## Purpose

Govern how PostgreSQL is accessed via Prisma in draft.io. Prisma is an **infrastructure concern only** — it never leaks into domain or application layers. Schema design supports the football draft/simulation domain with snake_case columns and UUID primary keys.

## Required Behavior

### Schema Location

- Single schema: `apps/backend/prisma/schema.prisma`.
- PostgreSQL provider; connection via `DATABASE_URL` environment variable.
- Run migrations with Prisma CLI from `apps/backend/`.

### Naming Conventions

| Prisma field | Database column | TypeScript (domain) |
|--------------|-----------------|-------------------|
| `displayName` | `display_name` | `PlayerName` value object |
| `overallRating` | `overall_rating` | `OverallRating` value object |
| `createdAt` | `created_at` | `Date` |
| `updatedAt` | `updated_at` | `Date` |

- Model names: PascalCase singular (`Player`, `Team`).
- Table names: snake_case plural via `@@map("players")`.
- Primary keys: `String @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid`.
- Add `@@index` for frequently filtered columns (e.g., `position`, `overallRating`).

### Repository Pattern

- Implement domain `*Repository` port in `infrastructure/persistence/prisma-{entity}.repository.ts`.
- Class is `@Injectable()` — this is the only NestJS decorator in persistence layer.
- Inject `PrismaService` from `infrastructure/database/prisma.service.ts`.
- Use `upsert` for save operations to handle create and update uniformly.

### Mappers

- Separate mapper file: `infrastructure/mappers/{entity}.mapper.ts`.
- `toDomain(record)` → reconstitutes entity via `Entity.reconstitute()`.
- `toPersistence(entity)` → plain object for Prisma `create`/`update`/`upsert`.
- Mappers are pure functions — no async, no side effects.

### Queries

- Keep queries in repository methods — no raw SQL unless performance-critical and documented.
- Return domain entities, never Prisma model types, from repository public methods.
- Use `findUnique` for ID lookups, `findMany` with explicit `orderBy` for lists.
- Cross-module data: fetch by ID in application layer, never join across bounded contexts in a single query.

### Migrations

- Every schema change requires a migration file.
- Review generated SQL before applying to shared environments.
- Never edit applied migration files — create a new migration instead.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Importing `@prisma/client` in domain or application layers.
- Returning `Prisma.Player` (or any Prisma type) from use cases or controllers.
- Business validation in mappers or repositories (belongs in domain value objects).
- Using Prisma models as domain entities directly.
- `prisma.$queryRaw` without parameterization.
- Storing domain logic in Prisma middleware.
- Cross-module `include` joins that couple bounded contexts.
- Nullable columns without explicit handling in mapper (`null` → domain default or error).

## Good Examples

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma
model Player {
  id            String   @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid
  displayName   String   @map("display_name") @db.VarChar(100)
  position      String   @db.VarChar(10)
  overallRating Int      @map("overall_rating") @db.SmallInt
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  @@index([position])
  @@index([overallRating])
  @@map("players")
}
```

```typescript
// infrastructure/mappers/player.mapper.ts
export function toPlayerDomain(record: PrismaPlayer): Player {
  return Player.reconstitute({
    id: PlayerId.create(record.id),
    name: PlayerName.create(record.displayName),
    position: Position.create(record.position),
    overallRating: OverallRating.create(record.overallRating),
    createdAt: record.createdAt,
    updatedAt: record.updatedAt,
  });
}

export function toPlayerPersistence(player: Player) {
  return {
    id: player.id.value,
    displayName: player.name.value,
    position: player.position.value,
    overallRating: player.overallRating.value,
    createdAt: player.createdAt,
    updatedAt: player.updatedAt,
  };
}
```

```typescript
// infrastructure/persistence/prisma-player.repository.ts
@Injectable()
export class PrismaPlayerRepository implements PlayerRepository {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  async save(player: Player): Promise<void> {
    const data = toPlayerPersistence(player);
    await this.prisma.player.upsert({
      where: { id: data.id },
      create: data,
      update: {
        displayName: data.displayName,
        position: data.position,
        overallRating: data.overallRating,
        updatedAt: data.updatedAt,
      },
    });
  }
}
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// BAD: Prisma in use case
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

export class CreatePlayerUseCase {
  async execute(command: CreatePlayerCommand) {
    await this.prisma.player.create({ data: command });
  }
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: validation in repository
async save(player: Player): Promise<void> {
  if (player.overallRating.value > 99) throw new Error('Invalid rating');
  await this.prisma.player.create({ ... });
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: returning Prisma model from repository
async findById(id: string): Promise<Prisma.Player | null> {
  return this.prisma.player.findUnique({ where: { id } });
}
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Schema changes include `@@map`, `@map`, and appropriate indexes
- [ ] Repository implements domain port interface
- [ ] Mapper functions handle domain ↔ persistence conversion
- [ ] Repository methods return domain entities only
- [ ] No Prisma imports outside `infrastructure/` and `prisma/`
- [ ] Migration created and reviewed for schema changes
- [ ] Cross-module references resolved by ID in application layer, not SQL joins
